Name: bladder squamous papilloma
Definition: A renal infectious disease and is_a Human immunodeficiency virus infectious disease that results_in infection located_in kidney

Name: bladder flat intraepithelial lesion
Definition: An ovarian disease where ovaries do not produce estrogen despite high levels of circulating gonadotropins in women under 40.
Synonym: Flat Intraepithelial Lesion of the urinary bladder

Name: nephrogenic adenoma of urinary bladder
Definition: A gastrointestinal tuberculosis that involves formation of tuberculous ulcers located_in esophagus. The infection has_symptom dysphagia
Synonym: Nephrogenic adenoma of the urinary bladder
